{:proof/problem-id "apm-t97A04", :proof/classification :partial, :proof/output "\n\n---\n\nTARGET SANITY CHECK — mentions-problem-objects? ✅ (the statements explicitly reference the torus, the map \\(L\\), and its induced actions on homology) · avoids-assuming-conclusion? ✅ (the target theorem states the conclusions to be proved without building them into the hypotheses) · meaningful-without-prose? ✅ (even without Stage 1 text the statements assert precise algebraic facts). Notes: linear-algebra viewpoint drives all three questions; helper lemma records the degree = determinant fact.\n\n```\nPROOF-PLAN.EDN\n{:goal \"Determine the degree, induced map on H₁, and Lefschetz number of the torus endomorphism induced by L(x,y)=(2x+y,y-x).\"\n :terms [{:name \"Degree/determinant\"\n          :meaning \"Degree of the induced map on T² equals det of the integer matrix.\"\n          :needed-because \"This answers part (a) and controls H₂ action for Lefschetz.\"}\n         {:name \"Homology basis\"\n          :meaning \"Use the standard generators [circle in x],[circle in y].\"\n          :needed-because \"The induced H₁ map is just the matrix of L in that basis.\"}\n         {:name \"Lefschetz formula\"\n          :meaning \"L(f)=∑(-1)^i tr(f_*|H_i).\"\n          :needed-because \"Combines traces on H₀,H₁,H₂ to get the final number.\"}]\n :strategy [{:id :s1\n             :formal-dependency \"lefschetz_number_linear_torus\"\n             :informal-dependency \"Take the 2×2 integer matrix, read off det and action on H₁, then plug traces into the Lefschetz formula.\"\n             :why-this-now \"Linear algebra directly answers all three parts without geometry.\"\n             :lean-target \"torus_linear_map_lefschetz\"\n             :mathlib-status \"Mathlib can express group endomorphisms on homology for tori via linear algebra, but a packaged Lefschetz-number API for general torus maps is not yet available.\"}]\n :stage-status {:stage1 :done :stage2 :done :stage3 :in-progress :stage4 :pending}}\n```\n\n```\nFORMAL-ALIGNMENT.EDN\n{:main-claim {:informal-claim \"For the torus endomorphism induced by L(x,y)=(2x+y,y-x), deg L=3, the H₁-action is given by the matrix (2 1; −1 1), and the Lefschetz number is 1.\"\n             :formal-name \"torus_linear_map_lefschetz\"\n             :formal-target \"In homology, L_* has degree 3 on H₂, acts via the above matrix on H₁, and yields Lefschetz number 1 by L(f)=tr(H₀)-tr(H₁)+tr(H₂).\"\n             :sanity-check {:mentions-problem-objects? true\n                            :avoids-assuming-conclusion? true\n                            :meaningful-without-prose? true\n                            :notes \"Summarizes parts (a)-(c).\"}}\n :alignments [{:formal-name \"torus_linear_map_lefschetz\"\n              :formal-statement \"deg=3,   L_*|_{H_1} = (2 1; −1 1),   Lef(L)=1.\"\n              :informal-clause \"Stage 1 conclusion\"\n              :role :main-theorem}\n             {:formal-name \"degree_equals_determinant\"\n              :formal-statement \"For a lattice automorphism A∈GL(2,ℤ), the induced map on T² has degree det A.\"\n              :informal-clause \"Supplies the degree/H₂ action used in Stage 1\"\n              :role :helper-lemma}]}\n```\n\n---\n\nTARGET SANITY CHECK — mentions-problem-objects? ✅ (explicitly references the torus map induced by \\(L\\), its degree, action on \\(H_1\\), and Lefschetz number) · avoids-assuming-conclusion? ✅ (formal target states what must be proved about \\(f\\) without baking it into the hypotheses) · meaningful-without-prose? ✅ (the statements stand alone as precise algebraic claims). Notes: helper lemma isolates “degree = determinant,” which feeds both the degree computation and the \\(H_2\\) trace used in the Lefschetz number.\n\n```\nPROOF-PLAN.EDN\n{:goal \"Determine the degree, induced map on H₁, and Lefschetz number of the torus endomorphism induced by L(x,y)=(2x+y,y-x).\"\n :terms [{:name \"Degree/determinant\"\n          :meaning \"Degree o